@NODE INSTALLING "Installing BServer"
 ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
 To install this program, you have to

 1) extract the archive (you have already done that ;-)

 2) copy the drawer somewhere in your hard disk

 3) extract one set of icons from the Icons drawer; this drawer contains
    the following archives:
    ñ NewIcons.lha (needed if you use the NewIcons package; normal icons
      are represented just with a small dot to save disk space)
    ñ New+StdIcons.lha (needed if you use the NewIcons package; normal
      icons work well but require more disk space)
    ñ StdIcons.lha (if you use normal icons)
    There is NOT a MagicWB set of icons. If someone wants to earn fame and
    glory, he can always send me that set ;-)

 4) Finally, the libraries part:
    More than a friend of mine a) does not like to put many custom libraries
    in the LIBS drawer or b) does not like to spread parts of a program in
    various drawers or partitions (i.e. they did not like to put BServer,
    or a mere copy of it, in the WBStartup, and the Catalogs in the LOCALE:
    directory). So
    ñ bitmap.library and client.library can be found in the Libs directory;
    ñ BServer itself can now be specified as a tooltype.
    You have to do the following:
    ñ if you want to start BServer at boot time, put a @{"list" link CLIENTLIST} of clients in
      the WBStartup drawer with BServer as default tool, with the DONOTWAIT
      tool specified and PRECISE PATHS to search clients;
    ñ install client.library and bitmap.library in LIBS:, or move them in
      the Clients drawer, as you prefer;
    ñ install BServer.catalog in your LOCALE: directory or leave it in the
      BServer drawer, as you prefer.
